#Text=Create a Drop Shipped T Shirt Website
#Text=Have you ever wanted to start your own T-Shirt company , but did n't have enough money to purchase inventory ?
#Text=Well drop-shipping is right for you !
#Text=Drop-Shipping takes all the production and shipment out of your hands , so you can focus on creating your T-Shirt designs and promoting your brand .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Create your Brand Name
#Text=Many people will gloss over this step thinking it 's not that important , but when it comes to clothing and design .
#Text=Branding is actually very important !
#Text=Come up with a unique name that fits your niche .
#Text=If you are having trouble , try writing down all the characteristics of your designs , potential customers , and of yourself .
#Text=Then just start combining words and see what you come up with !
#Text=Create your website
#Text=Head to shopify.com
#Text=Create an account ; You start with a 14 day risk free trial , and you can upgrade at the end of it .
#Text=2 weeks should give you enough time to expirement around with shopify , and see if there is any demand for your T-Shirts

column1: #Text=If you are n't looking to pay 180$ for a theme , any free theme will do just fine . ( You can always change this later )
#Text=Visit App Store
#Text=Start by pressing Apps , located in the bottom corner of the sidebar right above settings
#Text=Click " Visit Shopify App Store "
#Text=Install Printful
#Text=Search " Printful "
#Text=Install the app by pressing " Install this app " and follow through the registration process
#Text=Make sure the email used for registration is the same used for your shopify
#Text=Create your designs
#Text=No matter what program is used make sure the output is a PNG file
#Text=Required dimensions for a normal T-Shirt Design on Printful is 3000 x 3000 with 300 DPI
#Text=Below are settings that can be used on PhotoShop and Illustrator .
#Text=Other programs may have a different layout or different wording but the concept remains the same .
#Text=Upload your designs
#Text=Select PrintFul on the " Apps " page to begin uploading your first design
#Text=Begin by pressing " Add Product " at the top of the page
#Text=Select the products you would like your design on
#Text=Select whatever style T-Shirt or tank you would like ( Be sure to select matching colors )
#Text=Although this is a write up on how to DropShip T-Shirts , you can also select other products to put your designs on other products
#Text=Finalize the upload
#Text=Adjust the positioning accordingly , make sure your design is centered !
#Text=Select " Proceed to pricing " when you are done
#Text=Pricing
#Text=At this point , you could select how much profit you would like to receive from each shirt
#Text=Do n't be afraid to higher the prices , especially if the designs are high quality
#Text=Edit your title & description so that it looks as professional as possible
#Text=Once you are done , select " Submit to store "
#Text=I have my first designs uploaded , now what ?
#Text=Now comes the hard part : Getting customers
#Text=Try showing your friends your designs and getting feedback on how to improve your site
#Text=We live in a very social age , use it to your advantage .
#Text=Social media advertising is the most effective way to advertise your brand/product .
#Text=Research how to improve your search rankings on Google and other search platforms .
#Text=Do n't give up
#Text=This is the most important step of all .
#Text=Everything you have done would be for nothing if you give up after 2 weeks of no sales .
#Text=It may take days , weeks , or even months to get your first sale .
#Text=This is normal .
#Text=Stay Calm and trust in your designs .
#Text=Keep your site updated !
#Text=Keep pushing those designs , and advertise them on social media .
